{{! Why Work With Us Section }}
<section class="container mb-16">
  <div class="bg-zinc-100 rounded-lg p-8 md:p-12">
    <h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl font-medium text-zinc-900">Why Work With Us</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-zinc-700 leading-relaxed">
      At Redpencil, we know the common frustrations with data portals: they're hard to use, hard to maintain, and too often feel like dumping grounds instead of living tools. We solve this by focusing on usability, interoperability, and long-term sustainability. With experience in CKAN, our own data.gift, and custom semantic solutions, we'll help you set up or maintain a portal that truly works for your organization.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

{{! Three Types of Data Portals Section }}
<section class="container mb-16">
  <h2 class="mb-8 text-2xl font-medium text-zinc-900 text-center">The Three Types of Data Portals</h2>
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:gap-8 lg:grid-cols-3">
    <ServiceCard
      @illustration="/assets/vector/data-modeling.svg"
      @title="Metadata-only portals"
      @text="Think of these as catalogues: users discover what datasets exist, but the portal doesn't host the data itself. This is often the first step for organizations wanting visibility with minimal overhead. Best for: Quick wins, organizations with data already hosted elsewhere, or when interoperability matters most."
    />

    <ServiceCard
      @illustration="/assets/vector/open-data.svg"
      @title="Dataset-based portals"
      @text="These are the classic 'open data portals': the portal lists datasets, provides metadata, and offers downloads or APIs. CKAN is a well-known option here, and we can help you adapt and extend it for your needs. Best for: Governments, NGOs, and enterprises that need to share datasets with clear ownership and update cycles."
    />

    <ServiceCard
      @illustration="/assets/vector/linked-data.svg"
      @title="Resource-based portals"
      @text="Here, every resource—down to individual files, services, or linked entities—gets its own dedicated page and identifier. This approach unlocks true discoverability and supports linked data principles. Our own data.gift platform was built around this idea. Best for: Organizations that want to embrace linked open data, semantic interoperability, and fine-grained access to resources."
    />
  </div>
</section>

